 many case studies and interviews with fashion journalists working for newspapers, magazines, broadcast and websites, and with stylists, PR executives, photographers and bloggers. Their explanations of their roles and their practical tips and advice will be accompanied by analysis of examples of their work. The business of fashion and fashion PR will be explained for the trainee journalist, with the focus of the book being on offering practical guidance on how to report effectively on fashion - from sources and research to writing and layout. Each chapter will include suggested exercises and further reading. Covering every aspect from the law and ethics to using social media, from fashion theory to reporting the catwalk, this text offers everything a student or trainee needs to know to excel in fashion journalism"--</subfield><subfield code="c">Provided by publisher.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="596"><subfield code="a">29</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Fashion writing.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="949"><subfield code="a">TT503.5 .B73 2015</subfield><subfield code="h">GR_MACEWAN</subfield><subfield code="i">1007423997</subfield><subfield code="p">46.61</subfield><subfield code="k">AVAIL_SOON</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="926"><subfield code="a">TT503.5 .B73 2015</subfield><subfield code="w">LC</subfield><subfield code="c">1</subfield><subfield code="i">1007423997</subfield><subfield code="d">11/12/2014</subfield><subfield code="l">ON_SHELF</subfield><subfield code="m">GR_MACEWAN</subfield><subfield code="p">$46.61</subfield><subfield code="r">Y</subfield><subfield code="s">Y</subfield><subfield code="t">BOOK</subfield><subfield code="u">10/21/2014</subfield></datafield></record>